summary: Code creates a copy of the original function, then overrides the original function with new behavior and calls it to demonstrate the effect of copying the function.

details.comment: Code creates a copy of the original function, then overrides the original function with new behavior and calls it to demonstrate the effect of copying the function.
details.content:
def original_func():
    print('abc')
import copy
new_func = copy.copy(original_func)
def original_func():
    print('new_func')
    new_func()
original_func() # working!
